<hr />

<h2>ğŸ“˜ Overview</h2>
<p>
  <strong>RED EYES GITHUB BOOTCAMP</strong> is a classroom-ready desktop application that teaches
  <strong>Git</strong> and <strong>GitHub</strong> workflows through realistic, real-world scenarios.
  Instead of memorizing commands, learners practice the same decisions developers make on real teams:
  branching safely, opening pull requests, resolving conflicts, and working with remotes.
</p>
<p>
  This project was <strong>designed and built entirely by me</strong> as a capstone-level learning tool
  and portfolio project.
</p>

<h2>âœ¨ Key Features</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>100 questions</strong> across <strong>4 modules</strong> (25 questions per module)</li>
  <li><strong>No repeated questions</strong> across modules</li>
  <li><strong>Scenario-based explanations</strong> shown after incorrect answers (teaching-first design)</li>
  <li><strong>Final Exam</strong> unlocked after completing all modules</li>
  <li><strong>High-contrast GitHub-style UI</strong> with a 2Ã—2 module dashboard</li>
  <li><strong>Cross-platform</strong> (macOS / Windows / Linux)</li>
</ul>

<h2>ğŸ“¦ Modules</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th align="left">Module</th>
      <th align="left">Focus</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>ğŸ“ Git Basics</td>
      <td>Repositories, staging, commits, history, best practices</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>ğŸŒ¿ Branching &amp; Merging</td>
      <td>Feature branches, merge conflicts, team workflows</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>ğŸŒ GitHub &amp; Remotes</td>
      <td>Push/pull, PRs, forks, issues, collaboration patterns</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>âš™ï¸ Advanced Git Workflow</td>
      <td>Stash, cherry-pick, rebase safety, CI/CD awareness</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>ğŸ§ª Final Exam</h2>
<p>
  After completing all four modules, learners unlock a <strong>Final Exam</strong> that aggregates the full curriculum.
  This mimics a bootcamp-style exit assessment and reinforces long-term understanding.
</p>

